  "text": "Only one participant in the present study had E-folate concentrations below the recommended 300 nmol/L. Folate fortification in Australia may have been successful in increasing folate status of young women and confirmation will be required from national representative data. Despite the benefits of eradicating folate deficiency there is some evidence in the literature that high folate status may have undesirable effects such as, neurotoxicity and decline in cognitive function and epigenetic programming in utero [CITATION_1] .",
